David Bowie became the first artist to posthumously win a Brit award on Wednesday, picking up two accolades.Here are the winners:&#8211; British female solo artist Emeli Sande Other nominees were Anohni, Ellie Goulding, Lianne La Havas, Nao&#8211; British male solo artist David Bowie Other nominees were Craig David, Michael Kiwanuka, Skepta, and Kano&#8211; British album of the year David Bowie &#8211; &#8220;Blackstar&#8221; Other nominees were The 1975, Kano, Michael Kiwanuka, Skepta&#8211; British group The 1975 Other nominees were Bastille, Biffy Clyro, Little Mix, Radiohead&#8211; British breakthrough act Rag&#8217;n&#8217;Bone Man Other nominees were Anne-Marie, Blossoms, Skepta, Stormzy&#8211; British single Little Mix &#8211; &#8220;Shout Out To My Ex&#8221; Other nominees were Alan Walker, Calum Scott, Calvin Harris featuring Rihanna, Clean Bandit featuring Sean Paul and Anne-Marie, Coldplay, James Arthur, Jonas Blue featuring Dakota, Tinie Tempah featuring Zara Larsson, Zayn&#8211; British artist video of the year One Direction &#8211; &#8220;History&#8221; Other nominees were Adele, Calvin Harris featuring Rihanna, Clean Bandit featuring Sean Paul and Anne-Marie, James Arthur, Jonas Blue featuring Dakota, Little Mix featuring Sean Paul, Tinie Tempah featuring Zara Larsson, Zayn&#8211; International female solo artist Beyonce Other nominees were Christine And The Queens, Rihanna, Sia, Solange&#8211; International male solo artist Drake Other nominees were Bon Iver, Bruno Mars, Leonard Cohen, The Weeknd&#8211; International group A Tribe Called Quest Other nominees were Drake &amp; Future, Kings Of Leon, Nick Cave And The Bad Seeds, Twenty One Pilots&#8211; Global success Adele No other nominees&nbsp;-AFP